fields.descriptive_line: A collection of puppets and scenery used in the making of the television programme, Larry the Lamb', broadcasted from 18th September 1972.  The series was based on S G Hulme Beaman's famous Toytown characters. It was produced and screen written by Hendrik Baker.
fields.physical_description:
[Larry the Lamb 1] Figure of Larry the lamb.  Yellow and cream foam rubber over a wire framework. Black painted wooden hooves.
[Larry the lamb 2] Figure of Larry the lamb.  Yellow and cream foam rubber over a wire framework. Black painted wooden hooves.
[Larry the Lamb 3] Figure of Larry the lamb.  Yellow and cream foam rubber over a wire framework. Black painted wooden hooves.
[Larry the Lamb 4] Figure of Larry the lamb.  Yellow and cream foam rubber over a wire framework. Black painted wooden hooves.
[Larry the Lamb 5] Figure of Larry the lamb.  Yellow and cream foam rubber over a wire framework. Black painted wooden hooves.
[Larry the Lamb 6] Figure of Larry the lamb.  Yellow and cream foam rubber over a wire framework. Black painted wooden hooves.
[Letty Lamb 7] Figure of Letty Lamb.  Yellow and cream foam rubber over a wire framework, decorated with yellow and spotted red bows.  Black painted wooden hooves.
[Letty Lamb 8] Figure of Letty Lamb.  Yellow and cream foam rubber over a wire framework, decorated with yellow and spotted red bows.  Black painted wooden hooves.
[Dennis the Dachshund 9] Figure of Dennis the Dachshund.  Tan and burnt sienna foan rubber over a wire framework, painted rubber and foam head. Brown painted wooden paws
[Dennis the Dachshund 10] Figure of Dennis the Dachshund.  Tan and burnt sienna foan rubber over a wire framework, painted rubber and foam head. Brown painted wooden paws
[Dennis the Dachshund 11] Figure of Dennis the Dachshund.  Tan and burnt sienna foan rubber over a wire framework, painted rubber and foam head. Brown painted wooden paws
[Dennis the Dachshund 12] Figure of Dennis the Dachshund.  Tan and burnt sienna foan rubber over a wire framework, painted rubber and foam head. Brown painted wooden paws
[Small bird 13] Small bird, green and white foam rubber over a wire framework with a large yellow bill.
[Swimming duck 14] Swimming duck, yellow foam rubber with a orange bill.
[Goose 15] Goose, cream coloured foam rubber with a yellow bill.
[Arkville Road dragon 16] Arkville Road dragon, green foam rubber over a wire framework.  Green painted rubber and foam head with red detailing, Green painted wooden feet. Red tip to tail.
[Theatre Royal dragon 17] Theatre Royal dragon, green foam rubber, over a blockboard and wire framework.  Red tip to tail and other details in red.  
[Baby dragon 18] Baby dragon, (dennis in disguise), green foam rubber over a wire framework, painted wooden feet, head missing.
[Magician 19] Magician, foam rubber over a wire framework with rubber head and pointed wooden feet.  Wearing a brown smock with bands of contrasting colour and decorated with magical motifs.  It carries a white tipped magic wand. 
[Magician 20] Magician, foam rubber over a wire framework with rubber head and pointed wooden feet.  Wearing a brown smock with bands of contrasting colour and decorated with magical motifs.  It carries a white tipped magic wand. 
[The Major of Toytown 21] The Major of Toytown, a coarse foam rubber over a wire framework with rubber head and wooden painted feet.  The figure is dressed in eighteenth century style costume with yellow knee breeches and purple coat.  He wears a hat and a chain of office with a pendant badge made of a new penny piece and toy buckle.  
[The Major of Toytown 22] The Major of Toytown, a coarse foam rubber over a wire framework with rubber head and wooden painted feet.  The figure is dressed in eighteenth century style costume with yellow knee breeches and purple coat.  He wears a chain of office with a pentant disc of a woman's head in low relief and carries a golf club, his hat is missing. 
[Mr Growser 23] Mr Growser, foam rubber over a wire framework with rubber head and painted wooden feet.  The figure is dressed in Victorian style costume with green coat, yellow checked throusers and a top hat, he carries an umbrella.  
[Mr Growser 24] Mr Growser, foam rubber over a wire framework with rubber head and painted wooden feet.  The figure is dressed in Victorian style costume with green coat, yellow checked throusers and a top hat.
[Mr Noah 25] Mr Noah, a foam rubber over a wire framework with a rubber head and green painted wooden feet.  He wears a green belted smock and carries a staff.  
[Mr Noah 26] Mr Noah, a foam rubber over a wire framework with a rubber head and green painted wooden feet.  He wears a green belted smock and carries a staff.  
[Highway man 27] Highwayman, foam rubber over a wire framework with rubber head and black painted wooden feet (with large gilt shoe buckles).  He wears a eighteenth century costume of red knee breeches, a red double caped greatcoat and large red hat.  He carries a pistol in each hand and is masked.
[Figure in dress 28] Figure in evening dress, foam rubber over a wire framework with rubber head and black painted wooden feet.  He wears a black tail coat and trousers with a white wasitcoat, shirt and bow tie.
[The Mayor's secretary 29] The Mayor's Secretary, foam rubber over a wire framework with rubber head and black painted feet.  The figure is dressed in eighteenth century style costume with fawn kneee breeches and brown tail coat.  
[Punch 30] Punch, foam rubber over a wire framework with rubber head and black painted wooden feet.  The figure is dressed in eighteenth century style punchinello costume with yellow knee breeches and red, green and yellow punchinello costume with yellow knee breeches and red, green and yellow jerkin with a ruff.  The figure has a hump on his back and protruding belly.  He wears a red cocked hat with a curved crown and carries a truncheon.  
[The Inventor 31] The inventor, foam rubber over a wire framework with a rubber head and black painted wooden feet.  The figure wears a blue bibbed dunarees over a checked shirt.  He is hatless and partially bald headed.
[Ernest the Policeman 32] Ernest the Policeman, foam rubber over a wire framework with a rubber head and black painted wooden feet.  The figure is dressed in a blue police uniform.  
[Ernest the Policeman 33] Ernest the Policeman (riding a tricycle), foam rubber over a wire framework with a rubber head and black painted wooden feet.  The figure is dressed in a blue police uniform.  
[Tricycle for Ernest 33/A] Tricycle, constucted of metal plastic and wood with rubber tyresd.  The frameowrk is painted black and the wheels are silver in coloured.  It has a saddlebag.
[Toytown facade] Facade of Police Station, single storey surmounted by lower portion of sloping roof.  Pale yellow colour-washed wall with small areas of ashler masonry at lower corners and half-timbering immediately below roof. Roof consists of four courses of red tiles.  Yellow painted door with white door case to left, diamond pane casement window to right.  Ornate blue lantern by door.  large notice 'POLICE' (with handcuffs) below roof line.  The whole made of ply and other wood with metal support to lamp. 
[Toytown facade] Facade of Mr Growser's House, two storey's with a gable ended attic storey above; the roof of this storey continues back from the facade for a little way on either side.  The first and attic storey's are half timbered and overhang the ground floor.  White plaster covered walls.  Green painted door with double white-washed doorstep on left.  Casement windows with green painted frames (that on the right side of the first floor has a window box).  A lantern hangs on the wall next to the door, there is a green drain pipe.  Roof of pale shingles.  The whole made of ply and other woods with metal and plastic detail.
[Toytown facade] Facade of a two storey house.  Red painted wall above deep, cement rendered waterproof course (up to window sill).  Bay windows with blue slate roofs on ground floor on either side of front door (with stone step and brass door fittings).  Blue slate roofed porch.  Upper storey with large windows on either side of small central window (over door).  
[Toffee Tin] Toffee tin, printed in colours with scene of Toytown band marching accompanied by Larry the Lamb and a boy-scout.  Indented on base Made by Edward Sharp & sons ltd Maidstone, Kent.
